One of the few monuments dedicated to the late rocker Jimi Hendrix is a statue on Broadway Avenue near Seattle Central Community College in Seattle. The statue, entitled "The Electric Lady Studio Guitar", was made by artist Daryl Smith.

Opened in 1908, the Sorrento Hotel, is a local landmark that has undergone a makeover. The renovation includes a remodeled restaurant, now called the Dunbar Room. Jared Lovejoy, left, and Jena Thornton, are the designers responsible for the remodel. The remodel includes improved lighting and a new floor with tiles from Morocco.

The Seattle Monorail, which was built for the World's Fair in Seattle in 1962, runs on a one-mile route along Fifth Avenue from the Seattle Center to Westlake Center.The monorail travels through the Experience Music Project Museum at Seattle Center. The museum was built around the Monorail route.
